A store sells shirts in only three sizes (Small, Medium, and Large) and three colors (Red, Yellow, and Blue). A customer bought exactly three shirts from the store:

(1) Each shirt is defined by a specific combination of color and size;
(2) He did not purchase both Large and Small shirts;
(3) The store does not stock Small Red shirts;
(4) The store does not stock Large Blue shirts.

Which of the following must be false? ____

A heating station has five valves that control the supply of steam. The operation of these valves is subject to the following rules:

(1) If Valve 1 is opened, then Valve 2 must be opened and Valve 5 must be closed;
(2) If either Valve 2 or Valve 5 is opened, Valve 4 must be closed;
(3) Valve 3 and Valve 4 cannot both be closed simultaneously.

If Valve 1 is opened, which other two valves must also be opened? ____
